<div id="review_158235090" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/158235090" />
    <a title="Andy Perdue" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5157001-andy-perdue"><img alt="Andy Perdue" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1353476476p2/5157001.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/158235090?book_show_action=true">Apr 01, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Andy Perdue" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Andy Perdue" href="/user/show/5157001-andy-perdue">Andy Perdue</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/9667124-the-emperor-of-all-maladies">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5157001-andy-perdue?shelf=cancer">cancer</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer158235090" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5140400970875477334">This was a mammoth undertaking of research and writing. As a survivor/thriver, I found the book fascinating - and glad I live in the age I do. I think those who read this should also read &quot;Anticancer: A New Way of Life&quot; by Dr. David Servan-Shreiber. He&apos;s a two-time survivor who uses science to show how we can avoid/mitigate cancer, and it shows a side of the disease that isn&apos;t covered in this outstanding work.</span>
  <span id="freeText5140400970875477334" style="display:none">This was a mammoth undertaking of research and writing. As a survivor/thriver, I found the book fascinating - and glad I live in the age I do. I think those who read this should also read "Anticancer: A New Way of Life" by Dr. David Servan-Shreiber. He's a two-time survivor who uses science to show how we can avoid/mitigate cancer, and it shows a side of the disease that isn't covered in this outstanding work.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5140400970875477334" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


